# XVerse Remote Machines Configuration
# 
# SSH Key Authentication Format: user@hostname:port:remote_path
# Password Authentication Format: user@hostname:port:remote_path:password
# 
# Examples (SSH Key Authentication):
# ubuntu@192.168.1.100:22:/home/ubuntu
# admin@server1.example.com:2222:/opt/cuttlefish
# user@10.0.0.50:22:/home/user/XVerse
#
# Examples (Password Authentication):
# ubuntu@192.168.1.100:22:/home/ubuntu:mypassword
# admin@server1.example.com:2222:/opt/cuttlefish:secret123
# user@10.0.0.50:22:/home/user/XVerse:password123

# Add your remote machines below:
# ubuntu@192.168.1.100:22:/home/ubuntu
# ubuntu@192.168.1.101:22:/home/ubuntu
# ubuntu@192.168.1.102:22:/home/ubuntu

# Instructions:
# 1. Uncomment and modify the lines above with your actual remote machines
# 2. For SSH key authentication: Use format user@hostname:port:remote_path
# 3. For password authentication: Use format user@hostname:port:remote_path:password
# 4. Run with SSH keys: ./deploy_cuttlefish.sh remotes.conf
# 5. Run with passwords: ./deploy_cuttlefish.sh remotes.conf --password
